_des">Meta</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/02/18/business/00techfix-agents/00techfix-agents-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Derek Abella</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>You’ve Never Seen Ants Like This Before</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/05/science/ants-3d-scans.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/05/science/ants-3d-scans.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/05/science/ants-3d-scans.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The Antscan database captures the tiny insects’ diversity and shows how the world’s living things could be rendered in three dimensions.</description><dc:creator>Ari Daniel</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 05 Mar 2026 10:03:52 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">your-feed-science</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">3-D</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Insect</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Ants</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Research</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Nature Methods</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/03/04/05HS-tb-antscan-1235-cover/05HS-tb-antscan-1235-cover-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image" /></item><item><title>Anthropic’s and OpenAI’s Dance With the Pentagon: What to Know</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/07/technology/anthropic-openai-pentagon-dario-amodei-sam-altman.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/03/07/technology/anthropic-openai-pentagon-dario-amodei-sam-altman.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href=